EntityID

Gets or sets the EntityID property of the OptionObject.

Declaration
public string EntityID { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.String

The value is a System.String and can contain a myAvatar PATID, STAFFID, USERID, or INCID.

EpisodeNumber

Gets or sets the Episode Number property of the OptionObject.

Declaration
public double EpisodeNumber { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.Double

The value is a System.String and is used with episodic, patient OptionObjects.

ErrorCode

Gets or sets the ErrorCode property of the OptionObject.

Declaration
public double ErrorCode { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.Double

The value is a System.String and is used upon return to myAvatar to determine prompted response. Possible values include 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, and 5 as string values.

ErrorMesg

Gets or sets the ErrorMesg property of the OptionObject.

Declaration
public string ErrorMesg { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.String

The value is a System.String and is used to display a message to the user in myAvatar for ErrorCodes 1-4.

Facility

Gets or sets the Facility property of the OptionObject.

Declaration
public string Facility { get; set; }
Property Value
Type Description
System.String

The value is a System.String. For most organizations, this value is 1, however more complex security configurations will utilize additional values.

SystemCode

Declaration

System.String

The value is a System.String representing the System Code. The value may be SBOX, BLD, UAT, or LIVE.
